  "text": "The ion concentrations of SBF is nearly equal to those of human blood plasma (Na + 142.0 mM, K + 5.0 mM, Mg 2+ 1.5 mM, Ca 2+ 2.5 mM, Cl − 147.8 mM, HCO 3− 4.2 mM, HPO [CITATION_1] 2− 1.0 mM, SO 4 2− 0.5 mM, pH 7.40 at 36.5°C) [CITATION_2] . The SBF solution was prepared according to the Kokubo's protocol [CITATION_3] . The PEEK and 30 wt% HA/PEEK samples were immersed in 40 mL of SBF at 37°C in a humidified atmosphere. After 7, 14, 21, and 28 days, the samples were rinsed three times with distilled water and dried at 37°C overnight. Then, the samples were observed and analyzed with SEM and energy dispersive spectrometry (EDS; X-Max, Horiba, Japan). Furthermore, the concentrations of Ca and P ions in the soaked SBF were measured by inductively coupled plasma atomic emission spectroscopy (ICP-AES; Varian, USA).",
